:: Notes:
:: 1) The dates of public holidays vary throughout Scotland, and are set by local
::    authorities. The holidays specified here are those which are generally applicable in
::    most of Scotland. Each town or locality has other public holidays additional to these.
:: 2) Except for the Christmas/New Year holidays, public holidays do not in general coincide
::    with bank holidays.
::

:: Public Holidays
"New Year's Day"                weekend on january 1
"2nd January"                   weekend on january 2
"Early May Bank Holiday"        weekend on first monday in may
"Christmas Day"                 weekend on december 25
"Boxing Day"                    weekend on december 26

:: Religious

:: Financial
"Good Friday Bank Holiday"      weekend on easter minus 2
"Spring Bank Holiday"           weekend on last monday in may
"Summer Bank Holiday"           weekend on first monday in august
"St Andrew's Day"               weekend on november 30

:: Cultural

:: School

:: Daylight Saving
"British Summer Time starts"    on last sunday in march
"British Summer Time ends"      on last sunday in october

